docs/adrs/ADR-083-authorized-to-edges-for-custom-agent-authority.md:27:Create seed rows in `authority_scope` for agent_type="custom" with "propose" defaults. Custom agent creation would then only need `authorized_to` edges for actions where the user overrides the default. Rejected: this splits authority definition across two locations (seed data + edges). When a user sets "propose" for an action, it is ambiguous whether the permission comes from the seed default or an explicit override. All-edges-no-seeds is simpler to reason about and audit.
